entry.summary:
* Snow/pellet showers ongoing across the Sierra and western Nevada are expected to increase in coverage through the late afternoon. Snow accumulations will remain generally light areawide, but slick roads remain possible, especially in the Sierra. Expect brief visibility reductions under passing showers.
* A band of heavier showers looks to develop along a line roughly from Truckee to Hawthorne this afternoon/evening, with locally heavier snowfall up to 1-2 inches possible under this band. Increased instability this afternoon may also lead to embedded thunderstorms, with a 15-20% chance generally south of I-80.
* Expect showers to taper off overnight, with clearing skies leading to another widespread hard freeze Saturday morning.
